Cindy Cheung (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cindy_Cheung_(actress) 0 Cindy Cheung (born January 27, 1970) is an American actress of Chinese descent. She is a founding member of Mr. Miyagi's Theatre Company, and has an MFA in Acting from the American Conservatory Theater in San Francisco. She is the best known for playing the role of Young-Soon Choi in Lady in the Water and Elaine Cheng in Children of Invention.
